    "abstract": "<jats:p>Tuberculosis (TB) is considered a serious and signicant health condition in the World. Among the\nmusculoskeletal TB cases, cervical spine involvement is seen only in about 2-5 % cases. Cranial nerve\ninvolvement in tuberculous meningitis ranges from 20-30% with the abducent (VI Cranial Nerve) most commonly affected. Here\nwe present a case of isolated hypoglossal nerve palsy due to cervical spine tuberculosis which is a rarity</jats:p>",
